5|$|Southard {{was married}} to {{physician}} and <b>Wellesley</b> <b>College</b> professor Mabel Fletcher Austin, and they had three children. His interest in chess continued throughout his life, and he enjoyed intellectual gatherings {{at the home of}} art collector and friend Walter Arensberg. At the age of 43, Southard died of pneumonia in 1920 during a trip to New York City to deliver lectures to two medical societies.|$|E
