5000|$|She {{became a}} member of ASCAP in 1941. and was granted an honorary {{doctorate}} from Stetson University, in DeLand, Florida. Katherine K. Davis continued writing music until she became ill in the winter of 1979-1980. She died on April 20, 1980, at the age of 87, in Littleton, Massachusetts. [...] She left all of the royalties and proceeds from her compositions, which include operas, choruses, children's operettas, cantatas, piano and organ pieces, and songs, to <b>Wellesley</b> <b>College's</b> Music Department. These funds are used to support musical instrument instruction.|$|R
