5000|$|Sheehan {{has been}} {{described}} as [...] "one of the leading Early Music singers in the world" [...] by Marion Dry, the director of <b>Wellesley</b> <b>College's</b> music performance program. The Boston Globe has lauded Sheehan as [...] "superb: his tone classy, clear, and refined, encompassing fluid lyricism and ringing force". In a review of the Boston Early Music Festival's 2015 staging of Monteverdi's L'Orfeo, the New York Times wrote that Sheehan [...] "brought shining quality and deep sensitivity to the title role". During the Dallas Bach Society's performance of Messiah, the Dallas Morning News called Sheehan the [...] "best of the soloists", describing him as having an [...] "agreeably fibrous tenor deployed to great expressive effect".|$|R
